Name: occult macular dystrophy
Definition: A macular degeneration that is characterized by a central cone dysfunction leading to a loss of vision with a normal fundus and normal fluorescein angiography findings.

Name: vitelliform macular dystrophy
Definition: A macular degeneration that it is characterized by the disruption of cells in a small area near the center of the retina

Name: bestrophinopathy
Definition: A macular degeneration that is characterized by central vision loss

Name: patterned macular dystrophy
Definition: A macular degeneration characterized by abnormal accumulation of lipofuscin in the retinal pigment epithelium in a distinct pattern
Synonym: patterned dystrophy of retinal pigment epithelium

Name: degeneration of macula and posterior pole
Definition: A pulmonary tuberculosis involving inflammation that causes extensive thickening of the walls of the trachea with luminal narrowing.
Synonym: degeneration of macula or posterior pole
